Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.25,1:19:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,now you feel, oh God, I'm sorry I thought that. Oh, you know, dear, dear, you know, I confess that I
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.15,1:19:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,thought of killing somebody. That experience, then, is stored in the hippocampus. The hippocampus
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.47,1:19:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is where we store memory. So what kind of memories of the past does the person
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.89,1:19:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,who is not spiritual hold? Negative ones. Resentment, anger. He builds up a hit list
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.41,1:19:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of all his enemies, because it's memory. When he goes into memory, it's all of painful hatred,
