Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.60,1:20:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He's stored up in his hippocampus. His experience of the world was that of an animal. So the
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.28,1:20:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,unattenuated ego, then, is the animal. There's nothing in your ego that you don't see in the
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.39,1:20:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,animal kingdom. Everybody's ego is on display every day in Monkey Island. Territorial dispute,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.80,1:20:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,alpha males, who's going to get the alpha female, who gets more, bites, scratch, tear, hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.29,1:20:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at what people die for,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.51,1:20:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll show a thing from some place in North Africa, usually. As far as the eye can see,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.95,1:20:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing but dust and sand. Dust and sand. That's all there is. No water, no gold,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.17,1:21:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,no nothing. And they kill each other by the thousands. So who's going to own this?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.61,1:21:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They're dying over this? When you see pictures of it, you say, you've got to be kidding.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.27,1:21:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding. 500 miles of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.29,1:21:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,500 miles of nothing. They're going to kill each other over that. So the animal, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.77,1:21:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,unattenuated. This is consciousness level below 200. People above 200 presume that other people
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.38,1:21:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,are like you. I'm going to tell you something that's going to save your life and that of
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.52,1:21:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody on the planet. They do not think like you. They do not think like you at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.84,1:21:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not think like you. They do not think like you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.22,1:22:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll take your eye teeth, folks. Not because they're bad, because they're good. Good animals
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.52,1:22:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,take everybody's eye teeth. It's their duty, you see. I once applied for a job. It was
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.46,1:22:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in Wisconsin, too, I think. And you're supposed to sell peanut vending machines to retired
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.68,1:22:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,farmers. I think they're 25 bucks a piece. And the pitch was, you just go around and
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.82,1:22:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,collect the money. We've got a new version of that on TV. ATM machines and various things.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.84,1:22:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And you put them in filling stations. So the guy pictures,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.44,1:22:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,he's going to drive around in his old pickup truck and dump out all this money.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.64,1:22:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What you don't tell him is that only happens once a year.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.56,1:22:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's full of pennies, all right, but it takes a year.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.70,1:22:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So I got, you know, this is ripping off old people for their retirement money,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.34,1:22:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's completely fraudulent. And you know what he said to me, the training guy who was
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.48,1:23:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to sign me up as a salesman? He says, if you don't get their money, somebody else will.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.58,1:23:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that. If you think other people are like you, they're not. Because if they don't get
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.53,1:23:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,your money, somebody else will, is the prevailing message, okay? I don't want to make you paranoid,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.89,1:23:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,except it's best to be paranoid. Now, paranoia is what we substitute before spiritual vision.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.65,1:23:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say when the third eye of the Buddha body opens up, you have discernment. But until that
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.82,1:23:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,happens, you're anybody's company.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.38,1:23:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're anybody's victim. All right, above 200, what happens? The consciousness now shifts. So
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.48,1:23:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200, you got left brain dominance. You live in a linear domain. Everything is stressful,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.20,1:23:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,releases adrenaline. You get cellulase alarm reaction, resistance, and then finally exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.81,1:24:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You get cannons, fight or flight reaction. You're constantly reducing. It's an adrenaline world.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.97,1:24:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This suppresses the stress response.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.85,1:24:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It suppresses the killer cells and depresses immunity. It suppresses the thymus. That's why
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.51,1:24:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. John Diamond recommended the thymus thump. Because this blows the acupuncture meridian.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.30,1:24:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Repeatedly blowing the acupuncture meridian, because the various meridians are associated
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.44,1:24:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with various organs in the body, you're constantly interrupting the energy to the heart,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.00,1:24:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,or to the liver, or the stomach, small intestine, big intestine, whatever. You repeatedly do that,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.76,1:24:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and you finally kill yourself. Enough interference in the energy to the heart chakra, and the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.67,1:25:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to get heart disease. Okay, so you keep blowing the acupuncture meridians, and you end up
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.56,1:25:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with a negative physical state. Depleting is constantly shooting out adrenaline. You deplete
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.20,1:25:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the neurotransmitters in the brain. Which serotonin is the most effective? The serotonin is the most
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.36,1:25:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,common. You repair this with Prozac. A lot of people in our society suffer from a Prozac deficiency.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.10,1:25:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,At least a third of the population at some time during their lifetime will be seriously depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.49,1:25:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This is due to genetic factors. Genetic factors and depression and alcoholism tend to run genetically
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.72,1:25:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the same family. So if you've got a brother who's an alcoholic, the likelihood is about four
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.88,1:25:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,times higher that you may become depressed. So there's a genetic factor involved. There's a genetic factor
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.38,1:26:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,involved as well. Brain physiology and genetics. And what happens above consciousness level 200 now
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.79,1:26:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is in common parlance, you become a right brain person. We're talking about now is the right-handed
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.75,1:26:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,person as the standard model. Left-handed person is the other way. Above consciousness level 200 now,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.08,1:26:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the kundalini energy begins to flow. And now the same sensor input goes fast track, fast track,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.60,1:26:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,through the etheric brain to the emotional center. And your experience of the world is totally different.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.52,1:26:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Above 200, you think everybody in New York City is friendly. It's a fact. You can talk to any cab driver,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.27,1:26:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you can talk to anybody. I'll do it on video. I'll just walk down the street, stop any stranger, and immediately start a conversation with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.65,1:26:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell do you think of so-and-so? Right where they're talking to you like they've known you for 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.41,1:27:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like we know each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.73,1:27:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean? The cab drivers are friendly. Everybody's friendly. Everybody's helpful. It's a wonderful place.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.72,1:27:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because you're experiencing a different world. This is a different world. So this person now in the emotional center says New York City is a wonderful place.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.82,1:27:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He stores in his hippocampus the memory of New York being friendly and helpful and happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.22,1:27:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All the waitresses were friendly. The cab drivers were great. The hotel was wonderful. What more can you ask?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.42,1:27:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.80,1:27:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They actually live in two different worlds. So when I say, don't think that these people do not think the way you do because they do not live in the same world you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.80,1:27:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You think everybody thinks in the same world. That's very naive. They do not live in the same world you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.08,1:27:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, how can people indulge in so much hate? Well, it's because they see a hateful world.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.40,1:28:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To you, that's astonishing. To them, they're surrounded by enemies. So forgiveness comes out of understanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.55,1:28:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. They live in a world. They see that way. And that's why they think the way they do. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.68,1:28:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Their experience of the world is not the same. So to you, it seems crazy because you don't experience that kind of a world that would justify that kind of hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.87,1:28:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Blowing up busloads of children, bombing trade centers and God knows what all. Huh. Whatever they can think to blow up.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.00,1:28:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Conscious level about this.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.28,1:28:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level about 200, then the kundalini energy results in right brain dominance.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.74,1:28:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You now become dominated by the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.28,1:28:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, it's not what you say. You don't have to go through some kind of a ritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.60,1:28:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You become non-linear. You become the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.97,1:29:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You become the field. You begin to reflect the field and not the content of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.34,1:29:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you experience life as peace, you release endorphins instead of adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.20,1:29:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Endorphins are healing. They're anabolic.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.56,1:29:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Adrenaline is catabolic.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.99,1:29:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Endorphins are anabolic and tend to heal.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.65,1:29:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So kundalini energy is a healing energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.55,1:29:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It supports the thymus and the killer cells which fight off infection.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.23,1:29:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It results in positive emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.97,1:29:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The person is more peaceful, have greater immunity,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.69,1:29:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can say from personal experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.51,1:29:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,healing of the most incredibly impossible and curable conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.45,1:29:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is the most important thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.83,1:29:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens of their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.98,1:29:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The acupuncture system remains imbalanced.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.12,1:29:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If it does go out of balance, it quickly is restored.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.04,1:29:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a positive kinesiologic response.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.48,1:29:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And the track to the emotions is slower.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.70,1:30:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, the slow track is now to the emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.10,1:30:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The fast track is to the cerebral cortex
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.36,1:30:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and specifically the etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.74,1:30:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Specifically the etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.32,1:30:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So spiritual knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.51,1:30:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The understanding and learning is stored or is processed
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.40,1:30:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,through a special place in the prefrontal cortex of the etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.19,1:30:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just stated is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.32,1:30:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't read that any place, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.26,1:30:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard it hurt here.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.59,1:30:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you, it took me a long time to draw this thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.49,1:30:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I drew it about 18 ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.77,1:30:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I could not get it to be the way I knew it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.45,1:30:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally it came out.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.43,1:30:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.13,1:30:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is the conclusion?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.19,1:30:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The importance is.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.07,1:30:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's spiritual endeavor and intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.34,1:31:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Change the brain function, which changes how you experience the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.60,1:31:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,changes who you are, changes the body physiology,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.26,1:31:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,establishes an area for spiritual information in the right brain,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.35,1:31:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,cerebral cortex and etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.14,1:31:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When I told you, you're not the same as those people, you are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.70,1:31:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not the same person.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.02,1:31:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You are.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.76,1:31:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to field and we got fuel and content.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.22,1:31:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That sort of pulls together a lot, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.02,1:31:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Healing modality, physiology, spiritual work, kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.69,1:31:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It pulls it all together.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.38,1:32:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,See here in left brain, you're identifying with just this and this believes in causality
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.10,1:32:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and duality.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.80,1:32:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where a Marxist lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.60,1:32:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees the world as perpetrator and victim, see.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.03,1:32:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you begin to see that the worker and the capitalist are congruent.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.78,1:32:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The latest thing is to heap abuse on Walmart.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.78,1:32:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Woe to those who heap abuse on Walmart.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.93,1:32:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, anything that becomes successful in our world, you know, becomes a target for
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.38,1:32:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,abuse, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.68,1:32:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Walmart is no exception.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.84,1:32:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This week's issue of Fortune magazine, good or evil, is Walmart good or evil, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.06,1:32:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.28,1:32:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, the thing about Walmart is that it's so big and successful and a certain
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.16,1:33:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,segment of society hates anything that's big and successful, no matter what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.20,1:33:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, the question is who made Walmart rich and successful?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.67,1:33:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here made Walmarts rich and successful?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.95,1:33:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We all made Walmart rich and successful.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.15,1:33:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Show me the evil capitalists when we're the ones that did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.06,1:33:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We went there because prices were cheaper.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.38,1:33:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What about mom and pop?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.90,1:33:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, mom and pop get phased out, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.86,1:33:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When the telephone came along, the Pony Express died.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.36,1:33:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see evolution then goes through change.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.42,1:33:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean that there's a bad guy perpetrator and a poor victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.42,1:33:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that slavery passed as a human phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.44,1:34:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Slavery was widespread across the whole world for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.10,1:34:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In ancient Rome, the slaves outnumbered the free men ten to one.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.72,1:34:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the way life was.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.42,1:34:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it slowly phased itself out in various parts of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.64,1:34:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a transitor.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.64,1:34:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mandatory phase.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.64,1:34:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as women's position in society.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.64,1:34:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In an agrarian society, the woman's position was in the home and the guy was out in the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.56,1:34:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,field.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.56,1:34:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she want to go out there and sweat with the horses?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.30,1:34:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.33,1:34:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to go out there and sweat with the horses either.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.81,1:34:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In Wisconsin, they didn't have electric on the other side of the highway.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.79,1:34:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody had a milking machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.61,1:34:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody could afford a tractor.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.67,1:34:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You had a big horse.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.05,1:34:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And a plow.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.47,1:34:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And you were solid sweat from morning till night.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.94,1:35:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So he wasn't interested in washing the kids' clothes and bathing the kids and cooking and
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.96,1:35:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all that crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.96,1:35:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She took care of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.65,1:35:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother reigned supreme in the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.93,1:35:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Reigned supreme.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.39,1:35:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Modern society doesn't understand the position of the woman in the early part of the last
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.99,1:35:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,century.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.99,1:35:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially in the Midwest, everybody in Wisconsin knows what that means.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.96,1:35:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother, when a woman entered the room, you stood up.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.64,1:35:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You stood up.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.20,1:35:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And you honored her by opening the door for her.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.16,1:35:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother reigned supreme in the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.99,1:35:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And my grandmother would say, my grandfather would try to sneak through the living room
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.27,1:35:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with his pipe.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.27,1:35:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd try and hide it by his pants.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.39,1:35:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And she'd run through and say, Frank, Frank, the drips.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.37,1:35:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't allowed to use bad language in the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.17,1:35:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.17,1:35:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.37,1:35:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.41,1:35:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.51,1:35:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.53,1:35:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.59,1:35:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.69,1:35:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.77,1:35:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.89,1:35:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.93,1:35:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.05,1:35:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.53,1:35:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.73,1:35:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Women had a separate entrance to the bar in the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.84,1:35:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Men were vulgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.10,1:35:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They were at the bar.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.82,1:35:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They used bad language.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.88,1:35:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Women sat at the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.54,1:36:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And men watched their language around women.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.65,1:36:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see how respected they were?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.50,1:36:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They were loved and respected.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.16,1:36:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother was supreme.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.30,1:36:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Out in the field, the man ruled.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.28,1:36:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He ruled.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.20,1:36:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But he ruled over what?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.40,1:36:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The inanimate.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.50,1:36:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, machines and crap like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.30,1:36:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Horses.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.46,1:36:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoveling horse poo.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.46,1:36:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he was the king of shoveling cow poo
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.10,1:36:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,getting sunburned and all sweaty
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.81,1:36:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.44,1:36:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Saturday night you found out who was who
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.86,1:36:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Saturday night in Wisconsin
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.24,1:36:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to babysit all the time
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.38,1:36:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how I made a living
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.02,1:36:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can still smell
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.16,1:36:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the smell of it
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.20,1:36:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the kerosene light, the kerosene lamp
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.01,1:36:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,every house you went to
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.99,1:36:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,smelled like kerosene
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.95,1:36:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,then there was all those baby diapers hanging on
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.61,1:36:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the wood stove
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.63,1:37:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the big tub and the baby diapers
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.97,1:37:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so the place smelled of kerosene
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.93,1:37:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and baby diapers
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.77,1:37:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and sauerkraut
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.95,1:37:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but the woman, don't you see, was revered
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.26,1:37:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,she wasn't being
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.70,1:37:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,abused
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.05,1:37:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and kept out of the workplace
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.93,1:37:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,she didn't want any place in the workplace
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.31,1:37:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,she didn't want any place in the workplace
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.65,1:37:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,she wasn't being abused
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.67,1:37:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,if I said to my grandmother
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.49,1:37:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,would you like to get a job
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.93,1:37:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so she'd look at me like I was crazy
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.31,1:37:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,she had her job
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.33,1:37:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and she was
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.47,1:37:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so the woman was really
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.53,1:37:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way respected
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.99,1:37:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because she reflected an aspect of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.71,1:37:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that you don't get through the masculine
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.51,1:37:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,through the masculine
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.53,1:37:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you get the macho yang power
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.45,1:37:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was through the woman
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.60,1:37:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that you got nurturance
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.98,1:37:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it's nurturance by which we survive
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.84,1:37:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.37,1:38:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so I just wanted people to know how it really was
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.66,1:38:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,then after World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.42,1:38:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the woman was needed in the workplace
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.28,1:38:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and Rosie the Riveter
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.72,1:38:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we shifted around then because of Rosie the Riveter
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.90,1:38:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but again you see it's not victim
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.86,1:38:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to get past the whole victim perpetrator thing
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.30,1:38:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not an evil society suppressing women
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.64,1:38:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,women weren't even interested in it
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.56,1:38:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,my mother didn't hanker for a job at Woolworths
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.40,1:38:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.41,1:38:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the world I brought up in
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.18,1:38:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,if a woman had to go to work
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.56,1:38:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the man was disgraced
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.98,1:38:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a disgrace
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.22,1:38:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that your wife had to go to work
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.68,1:38:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.98,1:38:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to show you how
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.80,1:38:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,twisting a paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.08,1:38:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,makes a thing look like what it isn't
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.44,1:38:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you see
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.82,1:38:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't there's an evil perpetrator
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.70,1:38:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and an innocent victim
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.06,1:38:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody had more power
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.34,1:38:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,than my mother in the house
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.78,1:39:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,my father took his shoes off
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.57,1:39:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and you better not get mud on the rug
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.89,1:39:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and people went
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.91,1:39:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to work
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.03,1:39:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to bed when mother decided
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.68,1:39:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.65,1:39:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so power was equally distributed between the two
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.57,1:39:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody was perpetrating anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.58,1:39:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you see retrospectively backwards in time
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.44,1:39:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you can project the perpetrator victim model
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.58,1:39:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and what do you get out of that
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.92,1:39:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you get hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.16,1:39:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you get hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.77,1:39:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't get justice
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.87,1:39:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you get hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.82,1:39:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so what I meant to say
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.98,1:39:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.49,1:39:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.31,1:39:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see men and women as equals
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.81,1:39:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.31,1:39:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,all these positionalities are done
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.34,1:39:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,people get up there and they like to
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.34,1:39:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,grandstand
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.34,1:39:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because their ego loves causes
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.34,1:39:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing the ego likes better than causes
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.34,1:39:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,save the grasshoppers
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.34,1:39:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,save the forest
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.84,1:40:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,save women
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.34,1:40:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm always worried
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.34,1:40:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,where are they with the Iraqi women
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.34,1:40:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they're busy beating up
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.34,1:40:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the president about Iraq
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.34,1:40:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,where are the women now about the suppression of women?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.68,1:40:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in Iraq
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.68,1:40:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen a parade yet
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.68,1:40:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't heard anybody on television
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.68,1:40:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,these women can be killed
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.68,1:40:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,murdered at the guy
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.68,1:40:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all he has to do is say
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.68,1:40:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I divorce you
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.68,1:40:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you're done
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.68,1:40:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I suspect somebody told me
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.68,1:40:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you were flirting around
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.68,1:40:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,he can kill her
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.91,1:40:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it's legal
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.91,1:40:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,where's the complaint about
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.91,1:40:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you call out a woman now
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.91,1:40:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,where it's real
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.26,1:40:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,where women are really being repressed
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.26,1:40:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,they weren't repressed in Wisconsin in 1930
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.26,1:40:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.26,1:40:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so the field then
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.26,1:40:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.26,1:40:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.42,1:40:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.42,1:40:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.42,1:40:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.42,1:40:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.42,1:40:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.83,1:40:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.52,1:40:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.52,1:40:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.52,1:40:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.52,1:40:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the consequence of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.52,1:40:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so everything is coming about
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.52,1:40:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is the consequence of the prevalence of a certain culture
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.52,1:40:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain culture
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.52,1:40:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,precipitates out
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.52,1:40:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,just like
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.71,1:40:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you get beyond cause and effect
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.71,1:40:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,let's go on to some more exciting slides
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.71,1:41:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,if you get beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.71,1:41:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.03,1:41:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,well this just says what I've been saying
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.03,1:41:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll go on to the next one
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.03,1:41:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,see what
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.48,1:41:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what the future could hold for us
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.24,1:41:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in the next slide
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.73,1:41:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,what number is this
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.73,1:41:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,oh
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.01,1:41:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is the Louvre. Well, we spoke in Oxford, you know, this last fall, and a few of us went together, a spiritual group,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.57,1:41:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and here's the Louvre, which calibrates at 500, and in the middle is this abomination, this strange glass and aluminum cube.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.62,1:41:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is magnificent, you know, magnificent, and in the middle is this cube, modernism, calibrates at 180.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.17,1:41:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought it was interesting. Functionally, you can't beat it. Functionally, it's terrific.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.18,1:41:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It just looks really weird there.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.10,1:42:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something that was in the A.A. Grapevine back about 1950s, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.89,1:42:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It was originally in the A.A. Grapevine, which was a monthly publication in A.A.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.45,1:42:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It came out of the work of several people, and I think it's such a magnificent way of, in shorthand,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.13,1:42:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,dealing with teenagers.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.13,1:42:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Teenagers and adolescents and people, or even children, not to mention your own inner child.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.77,1:42:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the tree of self-realization. You see, it's built on the roots of worth, trust, kindness, gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.96,1:42:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all the source of the kundalini energy, which blossoms forth as creativity, purposefulness, health, joy, commitment, fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.86,1:42:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the tree of self-realization. To say yes to one's potential is to release the kundalini energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.95,1:42:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,which then manifests in all these various forms.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.78,1:42:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,To say no to it, to say no to it, to say no to it then condemns you to this tree here.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.84,1:43:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-defeating, mistrustful, paranoid, jealous, hateful, fear, guilt, self-pity, drugs and alcohol, crime dependency,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.03,1:43:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of conflicts. Bad enough it becomes apathy, a feeling of emptiness, alienation,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.72,1:43:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and mental illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.78,1:43:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's very simple. I didn't have this when I was working with the girls at Mingus Mountain.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.12,1:43:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But the last lecture I gave there, I finally retired from there, and I've got it meant to bring my watch with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.72,1:43:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I got one of those watches like you get when you've been with the railroad 20 years. Fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.52,1:43:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You push it, boing, and it tells you the time. It's wonderful. I love it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.42,1:43:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Got my name engraved on the back and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.32,1:43:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I gave a parting lecture, and I had just come across this.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.11,1:43:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It was sent to me by a gentleman that thought we might use it in our work.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.41,1:44:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I thought with teenagers especially, it's very simple to say,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.58,1:44:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,look, which life do you want, you know? You can have this tree or this tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.28,1:44:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It just makes it so clear, diagrammed, and obvious.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.50,1:44:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Which do you want? Drugs and crime, the recidivism, most criminals end up back in prison,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.12,1:44:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or you want a rebirth.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.72,1:44:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And emerge as a tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.73,1:44:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I like a quick visual like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.33,1:44:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we, I wanted to get a bunch of them made up for today,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.83,1:44:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because I think some of the people, when they see it, they just want one.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.83,1:44:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, some of our office staff, Gil, in fact, and Karen, made up.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.03,1:44:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I've got 20. We've got to put 20 of them out in the bookstore.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.83,1:44:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody wants them. But I just think it's just a great thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.03,1:44:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, if you blew it up to poster size and do it in color, and the original, this is green.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.23,1:44:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is green.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.03,1:44:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of very shades of brown.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.16,1:44:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's just a confrontation with which do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.76,1:45:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Which do you want? Which do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.34,1:45:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And it should make it very simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.56,1:45:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people who hate the green tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.38,1:45:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They do. They really are.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.28,1:45:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They say no to God, and they hate God.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.31,1:45:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And, so those who say no, that's your, that's your freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.30,1:45:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom is to say yes or to say no.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.70,1:45:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When you say no,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.50,1:45:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you cut off the flow of the green tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.70,1:45:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You cut off the flow of the Kundalini energy, and the consequences thereof.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.00,1:45:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But, isn't that neat?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.00,1:45:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we made 20 of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.10,1:45:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought maybe some of you from out of town.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.30,1:45:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get more made by the next one, and we'll probably put them on the website or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.00,1:45:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I just think, you know, for people doing work with kids, teachers and group therapists with kids and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.50,1:45:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this is Ralph.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.70,1:45:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is in the grapevine, 1952 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.30,1:45:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Came probably out of the work of Harry Thiebaud.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.90,1:45:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And, who else?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.60,1:45:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.30,1:46:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But, it's just a beautiful contribution somebody made to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.50,1:46:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we should take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.25,1:46:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And, then we'll do, I'll finish a few more things I wanted to say.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.68,1:46:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And, then we'll have questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.08,1:46:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As you know, we share, we share the dialogue with people with the audience.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.34,1:46:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People ask questions, and I answer them, and sign books, and whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.24,1:46:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And, the whole group shares with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.64,1:46:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.44,1:46:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know what's going to come up.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.97,1:46:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll take a break, and we'll meet again.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.74,1:46:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll do a grand finale.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.44,1:46:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.34,1:46:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if there's that great.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.69,1:46:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.49,1:46:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted you to see that.
